quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  10,79,"And the Pharaoh said, "Bring to me every knowledgeable magician.""
  10,80,"So, when the magicians came, Musa said to them, "Throw what you have to throw.""
  10,81,"So, when they threw, Musa said, "What you have come up with is magic. Allah will certainly nullify it. It is sure that Allah does not let sustain the work of the mischief-makers."
  10,82,"And Allah establishes the truth through His words, even though the guilty may dislike it."
  10,83,"Then, except an offspring of his people, no one believed in Musa for the fear of Pharaoh and his group, lest should prosecute them. And the Pharaoh was high-handed in the land and he was of those who crossed all limits."
  10,84,"And Musa said, " 0 my people, if you have believed in Allah, then, in Him put your trust if you are obedient.""
  10,85,"So, they said, "In Allah we have put our trust: Our Lord, do not make us a victim of the unjust people,"
  10,86,"and save us, through Yourercy, from the disbelieving people.""
  10,87,"And We revealed to Musa and his brother: "Have houses for your people in Egypt and make your houses worship oriented, and establish , Oalah, and give good tidings to the believers.""
  10,88,"And Musa said, "Our Lord, You have given Pharaoh and his group glamour and riches in the worldly life, so that, our Lord, they mislead (people) from Your path. Our Lord, obliterate their riches and harden their hearts, so that they may not come to believe until they witness the painful punishment.""